title: THE MANDALORIAN Episode 1 Breakdown, Theories, and Details You Missed! Season 1 Chapter 1
author: Think Story
comment: This actually felt like Star Wars. The sets were amazing, the characters were wonderful, everything looked just like the original trilogy. And it was funnier than I was expecting, which I appreciated.
“Initiating self destruct.” “STOP DOING THAT!” looking forward to the future episodes
I think "the purge" is referring to the imperial invasion of Mandalore rather than the Jedi purge
I am going to end all of my sentences with " I Have Spoken"...I Have Spoken

The idea that he "only cares about money" doesn't work, I think.  He's definitely after the money - he wants all the bounties offered, etc. - but the Armorer implies he's donating a good chunk of the Beskar to the tribe.  I get the feeling he's more honorable than most underworld types we've seen in SW.  The vibe I'm getting tells me he's very invested in the well being of his tribe of Mandos.
description:
Disney and Star Wars long anticipated "The Mandalorian" is finally here! I breakdown, review, and go over theories and details for season one chapter 1's episode as well as it's shocking twist!
